@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:4001/api/v2
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Get Admin Products (Requires Admin Login Cookie)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/products

### 2. Create Product (Requires multipart/form-data with an image, normally done via Frontend)
# Note: Testing file uploads in .rest files is complex. 
# It's better to test creation through the Frontend or Postman.
# But you can test validation errors without a file:
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/products
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="brand"

Apple
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="modelName"

iPhone 15 Pro
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

A cool phone
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="price"

40000
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="sku"

IP15PRO-01
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="category"

Smartphones
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="stock"

50
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--
